     6
     7- ** High Performance**: Rust-powered multithreading with zero-overhead abstractions
     8- ** Full Control**: Granular control over thread pools, channels, and async runtimes
     9- ** Multiple Paradigms**: Support for Crossbeam channels, Rayon parallel processing, and Tokio async runtime
    10- ** Memory Safe**: Lock-free data structures with atomic operations
    11- ** Benchmarking**: Built-in performance testing and stress testing capabilities
    12- ** Easy Integration**: Simple JavaScript API with TypeScript support
    13
    14## Installation
    15
    16```bash
    17npm install @swcstudio/multithreading
    18```
    19
    20## Quick Start
    21
    22```javascript
    23import { threadController } from '@swcstudio/multithreading';
    24
    25// Initialize the multithreading system
    26await threadController.initialize({
    27  rayonThreads: 4,
    28  tokioWorkerThreads: 2
    29});
    30
    31// Create a managed thread pool
    32const pool = threadController.createThreadPool('data-processing', {
    33  threads: 4,
    34  threadName: 'data-worker'
    35});
    36
    37// Parallel processing
    38const data = Array.from({ length: 1000000 }, (_, i) => i);
    39const squared = await pool.map(data, 'square');
    40const sum = await pool.reduce(squared, 'sum');
    41
    42console.log('Sum of squares:', sum);
    43
    44// Create communication channels
    45const channel = threadController.createChannel('messages', {
    46  type: 'crossbeam',
    47  bounded: 1000
    48});
    49
    50// Send and receive messages
    51channel.send('Hello from main thread!');
    52const message = channel.receive();
    53console.log('Received:', message);
    54
    55// Atomic operations
    56const counter = threadController.createAtomicCell('counter', 0);
    57counter.increment();
    58counter.fetchAdd(10);
    59console.log('Counter value:', counter.load());
    60
    61// Async operations with Tokio
    62const runtime = threadController.createRuntime('async-tasks', {
    63  workerThreads: 2
    64});
    65
    66const result = await runtime.delay(1000, 'Task completed');
    67console.log(result);
    68
    69// Cleanup
    70await threadController.shutdown();
    71```
    72
    73## API Reference
    74
    75### ThreadController
    76
    77The main controller class that manages all multithreading resources.
    78
    79#### Methods
    80
    81##### `initialize(options?: ThreadControllerOptions): Promise<boolean>`
    82
    83Initialize the multithreading system with optional configuration.
    84
    85```javascript
    86await threadController.initialize({
    87  rayon: true,
    88  rayonThreads: 4,
    89  rayonThreadName: 'my-app-worker',
    90  tokio: true,
    91  tokioWorkerThreads: 2,
    92  tokioEnableIo: true,
    93  tokioEnableTime: true
    94});
    95```
    96
    97##### `createThreadPool(name: string, config?: ThreadPoolConfig): ThreadPoolController`
    98
    99Create a controlled thread pool for parallel processing.
   100
   101```javascript
   102const pool = threadController.createThreadPool('processing', {
   103  threads: 4,
   104  threadName: 'worker',
   105  stackSize: 1024 * 1024, // 1MB stack size
   106  panicHandler: true
   107});
   108
   109// Use the pool
   110const results = await pool.map([1, 2, 3, 4], 'square');
   111console.log(results); // [1, 4, 9, 16]
   112```
   113
   114##### `createChannel(name: string, config?: ChannelConfig): ChannelController`
   115
   116Create communication channels between threads.
   117
   118```javascript
   119// Crossbeam unbounded channel
   120const unbounded = threadController.createChannel('unbounded', {
   121  type: 'crossbeam'
   122});
   123
   124// Crossbeam bounded channel
   125const bounded = threadController.createChannel('bounded', {
   126  type: 'crossbeam',
   127  bounded: 100
   128});
   129
   130// Array queue (fixed capacity)
   131const queue = threadController.createChannel('queue', {
   132  type: 'crossbeam-array',
   133  capacity: 1000
   134});
   135
   136// Tokio broadcast channel
   137const broadcast = threadController.createChannel('broadcast', {
   138  type: 'tokio-broadcast',
   139  capacity: 100
   140});
   141```
   142
   143##### `createAtomicCell(name: string, initialValue?: number): AtomicCellController`
   144
   145Create atomic cells for lock-free operations.
   146
   147```javascript
   148const counter = threadController.createAtomicCell('counter', 0);
   149
   150// Atomic operations
   151counter.increment(); // Returns old value
   152counter.decrement(); // Returns old value
   153counter.fetchAdd(5); // Add 5, return old value
   154counter.store(100); // Set to 100
   155const current = counter.load(); // Get current value
   156```
   157
   158##### `createRuntime(name: string, config?: RuntimeConfig): RuntimeController`
   159
   160Create Tokio async runtimes.
   161
   162```javascript
   163const runtime = threadController.createRuntime('async', {
   164  workerThreads: 2,
   165  maxBlockingThreads: 4,
   166  threadName: 'tokio-worker',
   167  enableIo: true,
   168  enableTime: true
   169});
   170
   171// Async operations
   172const delayed = await runtime.delay(1000, 'Done');
   173const tasks = await runtime.parallelTasks(['task1', 'task2'], 100);
   174```
   175
   176### Performance and Benchmarking
   177
   178#### Benchmark Operations
   179
   180```javascript
   181const benchmarks = await threadController.benchmark({
   182  dataSize: 1000000,
   183  operations: ['sequential_sum', 'parallel_sum', 'sequential_square', 'parallel_square']
   184});
   185
   186console.log(benchmarks);
   187// {
   188//   sequential_sum: { operation: 'sequential_sum', durationMs: 15, throughput: 66666 },
   189//   parallel_sum: { operation: 'parallel_sum', durationMs: 4, throughput: 250000 },
   190//   ...
   191// }
   192```
   193
   194#### Stress Testing
   195
   196```javascript
   197const stressResults = await threadController.stressTest({
   198  numTasks: 1000,
   199  taskDurationMs: 10
   200});
   201
   202console.log(`Completed ${stressResults.length} tasks`);
   203```
   204
   205#### System Information
   206
   207```javascript
   208const sysInfo = threadController.getSystemInfo();
   209console.log(`CPU cores: ${sysInfo.cpuCores}`);
   210console.log(`Rayon threads: ${sysInfo.rayonThreads}`);
   211
   212const perfMetrics = threadController.getPerformanceMetrics();
   213console.log(`Memory usage: ${perfMetrics.memoryUsageMb}MB`);
   214```
   215
   216## Advanced Usage
   217
   218### Custom Thread Pool Operations
   219
   220```javascript
   221const pool = threadController.createThreadPool('advanced', { threads: 8 });
   222
   223// Map operation (transform each element)
   224const doubled = await pool.map([1, 2, 3, 4], 'double');
   225
   226// Reduce operation (aggregate elements)
   227const sum = await pool.reduce([1, 2, 3, 4], 'sum', 0);
   228
   229// Filter operation (select elements)
   230const evens = await pool.filter([1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6], 'even');
   231
   232// Sort operation
   233const sorted = await pool.sort([3, 1, 4, 1, 5], false);
   234
   235// Chunk processing (process in batches)
   236const chunkSums = await pool.chunkProcess([1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6], 2, 'sum_chunks');
   237```
   238
   239### Channel Communication Patterns
   240
   241```javascript
   242// Producer-Consumer with Crossbeam
   243const channel = threadController.createChannel('producer-consumer', {
   244  type: 'crossbeam',
   245  bounded: 100
   246});
   247
   248// Producer
   249for (let i = 0; i < 1000; i++) {
   250  channel.send(`message-${i}`);
   251}
   252
   253// Consumer
   254while (!channel.isEmpty()) {
   255  const message = channel.receive();
   256  if (message) {
   257    console.log('Processed:', message);
   258  }
   259}
   260
   261// Broadcast pattern with Tokio
   262const broadcast = threadController.createChannel('notifications', {
   263  type: 'tokio-broadcast',
   264  capacity: 1000
   265});
   266
   267broadcast.send('System notification');
   268console.log(`Sent to ${broadcast.receiverCount()} receivers`);
   269```
   270
   271### Atomic Synchronization
   272
   273```javascript
   274const shared = threadController.createAtomicCell('shared-counter', 0);
   275
   276// Simulate concurrent access
   277const operations = Array.from({ length: 1000 }, (_, i) => 
   278  shared.fetchAdd(1)
   279);
   280
   281console.log('Final value:', shared.load()); // Should be 1000
   282```
   283
   284### Async Task Management
   285
   286```javascript
   287const runtime = threadController.createRuntime('tasks', {
   288  workerThreads: 4
   289});
   290
   291// Parallel async tasks
   292const tasks = ['download', 'process', 'upload', 'cleanup'];
   293const results = await runtime.parallelTasks(tasks, 500);
   294
   295// Timeout handling
   296try {
   297  const result = await runtime.timeout(2000, 1000, 'long-running-task');
   298  console.log('Task completed:', result);
   299} catch (error) {
   300  console.log('Task timed out');
   301}
   302
   303// Precise timing
   304const timer = runtime.createTimer();
   305// ... do work ...
   306console.log(`Operation took ${timer.elapsedMs()}ms`);
   307```
   308
   309## Integration with Katalyst
   310
   311This multithreading module integrates seamlessly with the Katalyst React framework:
   312
   313```javascript
   314// In your Katalyst application
   315import { threadController } from '@swcstudio/multithreading';
   316import { useMultithreading } from '@katalyst/shared';
   317
   318function MyComponent() {
