   333  
   334  // ... rest of component
   335}
   336```
   337
   338## Performance Tips
   339
   3401. **Pool Reuse**: Create thread pools once and reuse them for multiple operations
   3412. **Appropriate Sizing**: Size thread pools based on available CPU cores
   3423. **Channel Types**: Use bounded channels to prevent memory issues
   3434. **Cleanup**: Always clean up resources when done
   3445. **Benchmarking**: Use built-in benchmarking to optimize for your specific use case
   345
   346## Error Handling
   347
   348```javascript
   349try {
   350  await threadController.initialize();
   351  const pool = threadController.createThreadPool('safe-pool');
   352  
   353  try {
   354    const result = await pool.map(data, 'risky-operation');
   355    console.log('Success:', result);
   356  } catch (operationError) {
   357    console.error('Operation failed:', operationError);
   358  } finally {
   359    pool.destroy();
   360  }
   361} catch (initError) {
   362  console.error('Failed to initialize multithreading:', initError);
   363} finally {
   364  await threadController.shutdown();
   365}
   366```
